'''Mohammad Irfan Ismail''' (born 14 February 1992) is a Pakistani [[cricket]]er who has played {{Cric LO}} and [[Twenty20]] matches for the [[Quetta Bears]] and a single {{Cric FC}} match for [[Quetta cricket team|Quetta]].

From [[Quetta]], a city in [[Balochistan, Pakistan|Balochistan]],<ref name="ca">[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/192/192145/192145.html Irfan Ismail] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref> Irfan debuted for Quetta District in under-19 inter-district matches in mid-2007, at the age of 15.<ref>[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/192/192145/Miscellaneous_Matches.html Miscellaneous matches played by Irfan Ismail (44)] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref> He made his first-class debut for Quetta in February 2009, five days after his seventeenth birthday, playing against [[Hyderabad cricket team (Pakistan)|Hyderabad]] in the [[Quaid-i-Azam Trophy]].<ref>[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/192/192145/First-Class_Matches.html First-class matches played by Irfan Ismail (1)] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref> A [[Left arm orthodox spin|left-arm orthodox]] spinner and left-handed lower-order [[batsman]], he failed to take a wicket from 14 overs on debut. While batting, he scored five runs in the first innings and recorded a [[golden duck]] in the second.<ref>[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/204/204221.html Hyderabad v Quetta], Quaid-e-Azam Trophy 2008/09 (Group B) <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref>

Irfan made his limited-overs debut the following month, playing five matches for the Quetta Bears in the Royal Bank of Scotland Cup.<ref>[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/192/192145/List_A_Matches.html List A matches played by Irfan Ismail (5)] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref> Despite his young age, he served as the side's [[Captain (cricket)|captain]], with wicket-keeper [[Bismillah Khan (cricketer)|Bismillah Khan]] as his vice-captain.<ref>[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Articles/9/9517.html Squads for RBS one-day Tournament 2008-09] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref> Irfan took seven wickets during the tournament, with his best figures 3/57 from ten overs against the [[Abbottabad Rhinos]].<ref>[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/213/213933.html Abbottabad Rhinos v Quetta Bears], Royal Bank of Scotland Cup 2008/09 (Group A) <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref> In a later match, against the [[Karachi Dolphins]], he made his highest score, 17 runs from 22 balls. The Dolphins had earlier scored 364/2 from their 50 overs, with Irfan's opposing captain, [[Khalid Latif (cricketer)|Khalid Latif]], making 204 [[not out]], a rare one-day double century.<ref>[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/213/213934.html Karachi Dolphins v Quetta Bears], Royal Bank of Scotland Cup 2008/09 (Group A) <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref>

Later in the [[2008<U+2013>09 RBS Twenty-20 Cup|2008<U+2013>09 season]], Irfan played two Twenty20 matches for the Quetta Bears franchise in the [[Haier T20 Cup|RBS Twenty-20 Cup]], against the [[Faisalabad Wolves]] and the [[Lahore Lions]].<ref>[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/192/192145/Twenty20_Matches.html Twenty20 matches played by Irfan Ismail (2)] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref> He took only a single wicket during the tournament.<ref name="ca"/> [[Irfan Ismail (cricketer, born 1988)|Mohammad Irfan Ismail (born 1988)]], another left-arm orthodox-spinner, also made a first-class appearance for Quetta during the 2008<U+2013>09 season. To avoid confusion, Irfan Ismail (born 1988) is sometimes referred to as "Irfan Ismail, Sr.", while Irfan Ismail (born 1992), the subject of this article, is sometimes referred to as "Irfan Ismail, Jr.".<ref>(22 December 2008). [http://www.dawn.com/news/335311/regional-squads-named-for-quaid-trophy "Regional squads named for Quaid Trophy"] <U+2013> Dawn.com. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref>

